            <BSW-MODULE-ENTRY>
              <SHORT-NAME>SoAd_Init</SHORT-NAME>
              <LONG-NAME>
                <L-4 L="EN">This service initializes all global variables of a Socket Adaptor instance and puts it into the idle state. It has no return value because software errors in initialization data shall be detected during configuration time (e.g. by configuration tool). Furthermore, if a hardware error occurs it shall be reported via the error manager modules</L-4>
              </LONG-NAME>
              <DESC>
                <L-2 L="EN">This service initializes all global variables of a Socket Adaptor instance and puts it into the idle state. It has no return value because software errors in initialization data shall be detected during configuration time (e.g. by configuration tool). Furthermore, if a hardware error occurs it shall be reported via the error manager modules.</L-2>
